      "writtenOn": "2018-06-19T20:46:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "For any handler that you want to protect with the csrf package, you should allow only \"POST/PUT/PATCH/DELETE/etc. requests\". The csrf.Secure only \"[o]perates on a \u0027whitelist only\u0027 approach where safe (non-mutating) HTTP methods (GET, HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE) are the only methods where token validation is not enforced.\" https://github.com/gorilla/csrf\n\nThe examples on that page don\u0027t seem to do this correctly, so it\u0027s possible that I\u0027m misunderstanding something. But if you agree, I\u0027ll open an issue on that repo.",
